Business Times columnist Hilary Joffe and a panel of journalists discuss the stories making the news this week in the latest edition of Editing Allowed. The team takes a look at the possible effect of Gavin Watson’s unexpected death on the work of the Zondo commission, finance minister Tito Mboweni’s latest growth strategy aimed at digging the country out of its current economic hole and Naspers accusing the Competition Commission of hindering investment. Or listen to the full audio: Subscribe: iono.fm | Spotify | Apple Podcasts | Pocket Casts | Player.fm